<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1536597-spoiler-alert-so-does-the-man-from">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[(spoiler alert)<br /><br />So, does the man from the first short story survive? I assumed his boat sank, but then later on, there's a mention of the pregnant girl who jumped over the side of the boat, which made me think...how would anyone know about that if the boat sank? If everyone on the boat died, then nobody would have shared her story...<br /><br />Anyway, maybe it was meant to be ambiguous, but curious about others' thoughts. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
