<div id="review_3212347584" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3212347584" />
    <a title="Lekeisha The Booknerd" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10666444-lekeisha-the-booknerd"><img alt="Lekeisha The Booknerd" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1450269973p2/10666444.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3212347584?book_show_action=true">Mar 01, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lekeisha The Booknerd" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lekeisha The Booknerd" href="/user/show/10666444-lekeisha-the-booknerd">Lekeisha The Booknerd</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10666444-lekeisha-the-booknerd?shelf=2020-five-stars">2020-five-stars</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3212347584" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16690543942998780214">Whenever I read stories from Haiti, I learn a little bit more. No, I don&apos;t think I&apos;ll ever fully understand the country&apos;s history or its people&apos;s lives, but I love that I get to know it a little. This collection is beautiful, even when the stories are anything but. Krik? Krak! is some poetic justice for the people of Haiti. Love this!!</span>
  <span id="freeText16690543942998780214" style="display:none">Whenever I read stories from Haiti, I learn a little bit more. No, I don't think I'll ever fully understand the country's history or its people's lives, but I love that I get to know it a little. This collection is beautiful, even when the stories are anything but. Krik? Krak! is some poetic justice for the people of Haiti. Love this!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="16690543942998780214" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


